---

Boil a half-full #kettle.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat the @Basa Fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper.

Cut the basa into 4cm pieces. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw fish.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet} and @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}.
Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and
@Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Bring to the boil.

Lower the heat to medium and add the basa pieces to the sauce, stirring to
coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Simmer gently until the fish is cooked, ~{5-8%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The fish is
cooked when opaque in the middle.

Stir the @Peas{120%g} and @Honey{1/2%tbsp} into the curry.

Taste and season with more @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over your basa masala. Enjoy!